title: 2008 South Carolina Republican Primary vote count by county, SC, 2008
name: 2008 South Carolina Republican Primary vote count by county, SC, 2008
description: The map is based on uncertified votes" from South Carolina Election Commission website. It shows vote counts by county for various Republican candidates as well share of each candidate and ratio of McCain to Huckabee votes.  McCain won the primaries with 33% (138800) votes, followed by Huckabee's 30% (125175),  Thompson came in third with 15.7% (65840) and Romney came in fourth with 15% ( 63000). RonPaul at 3.7%  (15000). RonPaul at 3.7%  (15373) and Giuliani at 2.1% (8575) finished fifth and sixth in the primaries.      Note: one of the counties (Horry SC) does not have vote counts. Look for updates results later in the day. "
